{"id":"3970","name":"bright-early-twittering-no-more-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Twittering No More Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2010-02-17T09:30:00-06:00","tags":["district 7","emory river","erik cole","facebook","free and reduced lunch","hockey","hunger","kingston ash spill","kroger plus card","metro council","mnps","nashville predators","open meetings act","preds","ryan suter","SAD","seasonal affective disorder","second harvest food bank","shea weber","shell station","snow removal","social media","TDOT","tva","twitter","winter olympics"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/riffsyphon1024/4268468714/in/pool-nashvillest\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2757/4268468714_04481cfc10.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\"></a></p><p>Good morning, Nashville. If you&#x2019;ve been enjoying all the live-tweeting and Facebooking by some members of the Metro Council during meetings, you can consider it a thing of the past. The Council attorney <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/council-twitter-feeds-may-violate-state-law?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News%29\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">warned the twittering council members that such use of social media to inform the public could be a violation of the open meetings act</a>. Since some folks don&#x2019;t have access to Facebook and Twitter, the updates could be seen as a form of closed communication. It was a good run, but at least <a href=\"http://twitter.com/district7/status/9200291617\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Councilman Cole&#x2019;s</a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/district7/status/9205855349\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">string</a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/district7/status/9210142790\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">of snarky</a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/district7/status/9215481599\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">responses</a> makes things at least partially bearable.</p><ul><li><strong>A helping hand.</strong> Yesterday, we mentioned that many Metro Students were missing out on meals due to school closures. With more than 70% of students qualifying for and receiving free and reduced lunch, <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=11994754\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">we&#x2019;re happy to see organizations like Second Harvest Food Bank stepping in and trying to provide those missed meals</a>.</li><li><strong>Fang fingers!</strong> We know that lots of you, like us, have been glued to the Olympics for the past couple of days. We&#x2019;re <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/sports/preds-play-role-olympic-wins?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-Sports+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+Sports%29\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">incredibly proud of our two Preds, Ryan Suter and Shea Weber, who led their respective Olympic teams to a win this week</a>. Way to go, boys!</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces.</strong> <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/money/22583132/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Our electric bills will be going up again</a> in March &#x2026; In case you haven&#x2019;t heard, you can now <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=11994621\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">use your Kroger card to save money on gas at Tennessee Shell stations</a> &#x2026; TDOT is actually <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=11994118\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">$8 million over budget for snow and ice removal</a> &#x2026; A local psychologist notes that he&#x2019;s seeing <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=11995844\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">higher rates of depression among Nashvillians this winter</a> &#x2026; The TVA is <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20100217/NEWS0201/2170379/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">70% finished with the dredging of the Emory River</a>.</li></ul><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/riffsyphon1024/4268468714/in/pool-nashvillest\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">riffsyphon1024</a>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2011/01/19/bright-early-ease-on-down-the-road-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Ease On Down The Road Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Ease On Down The Road Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}